Giải thích GREEN WASH trong đề thi THPT Quốc gia môn tiếng Anh và xử lý câu hỏi có đáp án gây tranh cãi: 

 Câu gốc cần paraphrase:

“Exposing this deception is essential if clichés are to be replaced by real, measurable emission cuts.”

➡️ Dịch:
“Việc vạch trần sự lừa dối này là điều thiết yếu nếu muốn thay thế những lời nói suông bằng các hành động cắt giảm khí thải thực sự và có thể đo lường.”

➡️ Cấu trúc chính:
	•	If… are to be… → Diễn tả mục đích, điều kiện cần thiết.
	•	Ý nghĩa: Để có thể thay thế lời nói suông bằng hành động thật thì phải vạch trần sự lừa dối (greenwashing).

⸻

 Phân tích cấu trúc từng đáp án:

⸻

✅ B. Genuine efforts to reduce emissions cannot take the place of rhetoric without greenwashing being uncovered.

➤ Giải thích cấu trúc:
	•	cannot take the place of = không thể thay thế cho
	•	without + V-ing = nếu không có… → cấu trúc điều kiện ngầm (ẩn)

➤ Dịch:

“Những nỗ lực thực sự nhằm cắt giảm khí thải không thể thay thế cho những lời nói suông nếu như greenwashing không bị vạch trần.”

➤ Tại sao đúng:
	•	Câu này giữ nguyên mối quan hệ điều kiện giống câu gốc:
→ “Nếu không vạch trần greenwashing, thì không thể thay lời nói suông bằng hành động thật.”
	•	without greenwashing being uncovered → đúng với ý “exposing this deception is essential”.
	•	Logic đúng: Hành động thật sẽ không thể thay thế lời nói suông nếu chưa vạch trần sự giả dối.

✔ Bám sát cả nghĩa lẫn logic của câu gốc.

⸻

❌ A. Were it not for genuine efforts to reduce emissions, rhetoric about greenwashing could not be brought to light.

➤ Giải thích cấu trúc:
	•	Were it not for + Noun,… = If it were not for… → điều kiện loại 2, mang nghĩa “Nếu không nhờ…”
	•	could not be brought to light = không thể được đưa ra ánh sáng (không thể bị phát hiện)

➤ Dịch:

“Nếu không nhờ những nỗ lực thực sự nhằm cắt giảm khí thải, thì các luận điệu về việc vạch trần greenwashing đã không thể được đưa ra ánh sáng.”

➤ Tại sao sai:
	•	Ngược hướng logic:
→ Câu gốc nói rằng “Phải vạch trần greenwashing thì mới thay được lời nói suông bằng hành động thật.”
→ Câu A lại nói “Nếu không có hành động thật thì không thể phát hiện ra greenwashing”, nghĩa là phải có hành động trước rồi mới vạch trần → ngược logic với câu gốc.
	•	Sai trọng tâm:
→ Câu gốc nhấn mạnh vào việc vạch trần greenwashing là điều kiện cần.
→ Câu A lại nhấn mạnh “nỗ lực thật” là điều kiện để phát hiện ra greenwashing, điều này không đúng với ý bài.#learnontiktok

The EU is coming out with a greenwashing ban. Greenwashing is a term used to describe false or misleading claims made by an organization anout the positive impact that a company, product, or service has on the environment.  This ban is designed to help consumers spot greenwashing. A 2021 poll across four EU countries revealed that 53% of consumers can’t identify greenwashing claims on product packaging.
What will this affect? This will affect different industries, essentially all companies that sell consumer products. Including the food and beverage sector, travel industry, fashion brands and technology companies.
The goal is to ban generic environmental claims unless companies can provide proof of excellent environmental performance relative to the claim. 
What does this have to do with food labels? 
A lot of food products have marketing claims on the front of their packaging that don’t necessarily line up with the ingredients label. This makes it confusing for consumers to actually know what is in their food because they are being fed inaccurate information. It will increase the transparency of food labeling, allowing consumers to be correctly informed about the food products they are buying. It also forces the food industry to actually take steps towards making their products environmentally friendly. The new rules are putting some order in the green claims’ chaos. Companies will have to explain why a product is environmentally friendly. This is crucial if we are to guide consumers to make more sustainable consumption choices.
If and when the directive does get approved, EU member states will have 24 months to implement changes and incorporate the new rules into their law. This means that, if greenlit, many forms of greenwashing will effectively be banned in the EU by 2026.

This product is a prime example of greenwashing, y’all!

If you aren’t familiar with greenwashing, it’s when
companies use unregulated marketing terms such as
“pure”, “clean”, “plant-based” etc. which actuallv have no legal definition. They do this to persuade consumers into thinking that their product is a safer choice. Due to lack of labeling laws + product regulation, it’s completely legal for companies to do this.

Unfortunately, greenwashing is abundant. Most of the products sold on store shelves contain seriously
harmful ingredients that are toxic and known human
carcinogens.

This Tide product claims to be pure, clean, plant-
based, and gentle on skin. However, when you look at the listed ingredients that couldn’t be further from the truth. Here’s a break down of just a few of those
ingredients:

❌Fragrance - an umbrella term that includes up to
3,000 chemicals (usually phthalates) that have been
linked to hundreds of conditions including infertility and various cancers.

❌Sodium Laury| Sulfate (SLS/SLES) - a surfactant
known to cause reproductive organ toxicity, developmental toxicity, and allergens such as skin,
eyes, or lung irritation.

❌Polyethyleneimine Alkoxylate - an ethylene oxide
that is a well known human carcinogen that’s been
directly linked to leukemia, nervous system damage,
genetic defects, other various cancers, infertility,
reproductive toxicity, respiratory disorders, and many other serious health conditions.

This is why it’s SO IMPORTANT to read labels and not just go off of marketing terms!

Corporate “Greenwashing”: Is That Big Business as Environmentally Friendly as It Seems?

What even is greenwashing?

In #greenwashing, a company stretches the truth about how environmentally friendly they are. They might claim that they are using recycled materials or making more sustainable clothing. They might say they are reducing water consumption in manufacturing or diverting materials from landfills — when they really aren’t.

A recent survey by Google Cloud found that 72% of business leaders in North America believe their companies have been pretending to be more environmentally friendly than they actually are, just to attract customers who care about the environment.

We want to help you recognize corporate “greenwashing” so you can be more informed and understand what to do when faced with misinformation of any kind.

✨Slow Fashion Tip: How To Remove Yellow Stains From White Clothing: ✨

Let’s remember: as we nurture our clothes, they reciprocate by gracing us with extended vitality.

As I embrace a slower pace and more mindful lifestyle, I am discovering more and more that there is practical magic to be found in even the most mundane of tasks. Through this lens, basic laundry transforms into a meditative practice, honoring both our garments and the planet.

MATERIALS
- Blue Dawn Dish Soap
- Hydrogen Peroxide
- Baking Soda

✨STEPS✨

1. Mix equal parts dish soap and peroxide in a small bowl.
2. Fully submerge the stained area of your garment within the soap and peroxide mixture
3. Gently scrub away at the stained area.
4. For stubborn or set stains, lightly apply a layer of baking soda.
5. Leave your garment to set in a sunny area for at least 1 hour.
6. Wash your garment as usual.
7. If the stain persists, repeat these steps again BEFORE drying the garment.
8. Machine or air dry once the stain has fully vanished.

This is the beauty of the slow path: it encourages us to adopt a practice of consumption that lasts. I hope this laundry tip helps you on your slow fashion journey. Now it’s your turn! What’s your go-to sustainable clothing care tip? Sound off in the comments!

Replying to @sazzorak This is a dry cleaners guide to removing old yellow stains that usually show up at the underarm and collar of white tee shirts. Here is what you need:

Dish soap, all purpose stain remover, hydrogen peroxide OR powdered oxygen bleach, and some patience

1) Pretreat the soiled areas with warm water and dish soap (1 cup to 1 drop of dish soap)
2) Pretreat the soiled areas with your stain removing spray. Let it sit for an hour if you can.
3) Wash as recommended by the care label. 
4) Spray 3% HP on the entire garment and let it air dry OR
5) Soak the garment in hot water and powdered oxygen bleach overnight
6) Rewash

Oxygen bleach is also known as color safe bleach or non chlorine bleach. It takes lots of time to work so be patient! 

I do hope this guide helps, happy cleaning  

#yellowstains #stain #sweatstain #collarstain #laundry #laundryhacks #laundrytips #stainremoval

Hydrogen peroxide should be a staple of your laundry routine. It's very inexpensive, has a ton of different uses, and is extremely easy to use. 

To fix yellowing, or remove a stains color, simply spray on 3% hydrogen peroxide and let it air dry inside. Don't expect to see results until about 4-8 hours later. Repeat the process as needed.

It's always wise to check a garment's care label to ensure it's washable before using hydrogen peroxide, since it's 97% water. If you are unsure, test what you plan to use in a small hidden area first! 

For more horsepower, try using powdered oxygen bleach and hot water soaks. Sodium percarbonate creates hydrogen peroxide when exposed to hot water. This is a great strategy if you want to whiten a ton of things at once. Just make sure they soak overnight :)

Greenwashing can be easier to spot once you know what to look for. Read on to learn 5 ways a product might not be as sustainable as it seems.

 The product is literally green, or has natural imagery (like flowers, or it looks like bamboo but is really plastic). Color is a powerful tool in marketing, and people usually associate the color green with sustainability.

 It’s a plastic-free product but is shipped in plastic packaging. Kind of defeats the purpose, right?

 It’s a huge corporation that has a “green” or “conscious” product line. Or it’s a brand with a parent company who may care more about profits than the planet.

 It’s “refillable” …but the refills come in plastic. We’re trying to eliminate single-use plastic, not create more of it!

️ It uses buzz words like “Cruelty-Free and Vegan” without being backed up by a third party certification. Check for the official cruelty-free logos on the packaging.

With the rise of conscious consumers, more and more marketing efforts will be aimed at making products seem more sustainable than they really are. Our best advice is to do a little digging when it comes to products — it will become clear which companies say they’re sustainable and have the actions to back it up.

Greenwashing – Khi tính bền vững bị biến thành công cụ tiếp thị.

Trong bối cảnh biến đổi khí hậu và ô nhiễm môi trường ngày càng nghiêm trọng, người tiêu dùng đang ưu tiên lựa chọn những sản phẩm và thương hiệu “xanh” – thân thiện với môi trường. Tuy nhiên, điều này cũng dẫn đến sự gia tăng của hiện tượng greenwashing (tạm dịch: “tẩy xanh”).

Greenwashing là hành vi doanh nghiệp sử dụng ngôn từ, hình ảnh hoặc chiến dịch truyền thông để tạo cảm giác họ đang hành động vì môi trường, trong khi thực tế lại không có thay đổi đáng kể, hoặc thậm chí vẫn duy trì các hoạt động gây hại cho môi trường.

Ví dụ, một công ty có thể quảng bá mạnh mẽ việc sử dụng bao bì tái chế, nhưng không công khai dữ liệu phát thải CO₂, hoặc né tránh các tiêu chuẩn bền vững rõ ràng. Điều này không chỉ đánh lạc hướng người tiêu dùng mà còn gây tổn hại đến niềm tin vào các cam kết xanh thực sự.

Để tránh bị cuốn theo “làn sóng xanh giả”, người tiêu dùng cần tỉnh táo, tìm hiểu kỹ thông tin và yêu cầu sự minh bạch từ các doanh nghiệp. Tính bền vững không nên chỉ là hình ảnh – mà cần là hành động cụ thể và nhất quán.

Pinkwashing is a form of propaganda where governments or organizations highlight their LGBTQ+ friendliness to distract from or downplay their human rights abuses. The Israeli government and Zionist advocates frequently use pinkwashing by promoting Israel’s progressive LGBTQ+ policies—such as legal same-sex activity and limited recognition of same-sex partnerships—to frame the state as a liberal, tolerant democracy, especially in contrast to neighboring Arab or Muslim-majority regions.

This strategy deflects attention from Israel’s ongoing occupation, apartheid, and violence against Palestinians, and attempts to divide queer solidarity by painting Palestinians—and by extension, Arabs and Muslims—as inherently homophobic or backwards. This narrative is both racist and misleading.

Queer Palestinians do exist. They live under occupation and colonial violence just like their straight counterparts—and often face layered struggles due to their identities. Painting Israel as a “queer haven” while ignoring its military oppression and genocide of Palestinians reinforces harmful stereotypes and justifies violence under the guise of tolerance.

Regardless of a society’s stance on queerness, the fight for LGBTQ+ liberation must reject pinkwashing and settler colonialism. If we truly believe in queer liberation, we must stand in solidarity with Palestine. None of us are free until ALL of us are free. #fyp#foryou#lesbian#freepalestine##queer#leftist#pinkwashing

GRWM while I talk about what the word “whitewashed” means to me.

This may be a controversial hot take, but because of my appearance and “asian american accent” I have always been labeled “whitewashed”.

I don’t understand why we don’t find that word offensive. Correct me if I am stepping out of line; but why do I have to look and act a certain way just because of my race?

Why am I expected to hold up to a certain standard then other people just because of what I look like?

You don’t have to confine to racial stereotypes. You are so much more than your skin color. You are your own person. You can like the same hobbies, same clothes, same makeup products regardless of where you came from.

I am told “racism doesn’t exist anymore”, but it still hits me when my race defines who I am. 

Let’s stop the stereotypes. We aren’t just the “black friend”, “asian friend”, “mexican friend”, “european friend”, etc. We are just friends.

As cringe as it sounds, we are all just people. We all bleed the same.

Gut health starts before you eat, it starts with how you clean your food  Most produce (even organic) is coated in pesticide residue, bacteria, and waxes that can disrupt your gut microbiome over time. This is how I wash mine  1. Fill a glass or ceramic bowl (never plastic — it often leeches chemicals) 2. Add filtered, tepid-to-warm water 3. Pour in white vinegar — 3 parts water to 1 part vinegar 4. Add baking soda if you want extra scrubbing power (especially for apples, potatoes, etc) 5. Massage gently, then let soak for 10 minutes 6. Rinse thoroughly Water temp tips : Tepid/warm: best for most firm fruits + veg Cool/cold: for delicate items like berries to avoid mushiness  Storage: Let your produce air dry fully, then store in glass containers to keep them fresher for longer (and reduce chemical exposure from plastic). I do this even with organic produce — because let’s be honest, the standards are low and labels aren’t always reliable  #guthealth #holistichealth #lowtoxliving #holisticnutrition #nontoxicliving #guthealing #guthealthcoach

Washing your toothbrush with soap and water each night can significantly reduce the accumulation of bacteria, viruses, and fungi on its bristles and handle. This practice helps prevent the introduction of bacteria, viruses and fungi in the mouth. Also, recent studies have suggested a link between oral bacteria and cardiovascular health, indicating that maintaining oral hygiene might also contribute to heart health. So, a clean toothbrush is more effective at removing plaque, which is crucial not only for dental health but potentially for preventing cardiovascular disease as well. It’s important to thoroughly rinse the toothbrush to remove any soap before use to ensure safety. #dental  #hearthealth #healthtips #healthyliving #doctor

Tenía que mostrarlo. La realidad de Galápagos no es como la pintan… ️

Para ser sincera, durante mi tiempo en Galápagos, tuve ecoansiedad grave. Esperaba un paraíso, un lugar donde las cosas funcionaran bien… pero me di cuenta de que no podíamos grabarlo como un ejemplo para el mundo. Y eso nos rompió el corazón. 

Últimamente, he recibido comentarios diciendo que solo critico y quiero destruir países… pero eso no es verdad. 
Mi contenido es real. Muestro lo bueno y lo malo, porque si no hablamos de los problemas, nadie los soluciona.

Nadie quiere escuchar lo negativo, pero si tengo el poder de abrir los ojos, lo voy a hacer. 
Cuando publico una limpieza en grupo o algo positivo, nadie lo ve. Pero si esto es lo que se viraliza, voy a aprovecharlo para despertar conciencia.

Pueden llamarme como quieran, amenazarme… pero no me voy a callar. 
No quiero que esto los deprima, quiero que los motive a actuar.

Si algo te molesta, háblalo. Denúncialo. ️ No esperes hasta que sea demasiado tarde.
Si tu lucha es el medio ambiente, la salud mental, la alimentación o cualquier otro tema… hazlo visible.
Porque no estás solo. Y esto es la esperanza. Ustedes me la dan, con sus mensajes, sus acciones, sus proyectos.

 Nosotros nunca vamos a parar.
 Ellos son mi fuerza: lobos marinos, iguanas, perezosos, toda la naturaleza que sufre. 
Voy a ser su voz y voy a ayudarles. Sé que ustedes están conmigo.

 ¿Te animas a empezar ya?
♻️ Cada acción cuenta.

Piece 3 of 7 in my first seriesLAVADO MARRÓN
“Amor de Madre” (I had to )

The Pazzi Madonna by Donatello is a tender yet somber relief sculpture, carved in marble, depicting the Virgin Mary holding the infant Christ. Unlike grand, idealized portrayals of motherhood, Donatello captures a quiet, intimate moment—Mary’s downcast eyes and solemn expression reflecting a deep sense of sorrow and contemplation. The piece embodies themes of maternal love, sacrifice, and the weight of destiny.

In my recreation, I reimagined this moment through the lens of Chicano motherhood. Rather than a sorrowful gaze, I gave the mother an expression of love and adoration—one of pride, not fear. As a mother, I don’t see hopelessness when I look at my children. I see the future. It’s easy to be overwhelmed by the darkness of the world, but our children are the light, the voices of change. They deserve to be fiercely protected, nurtured, and empowered.

I portrayed the mother as a traditional Mexican woman, dressed simply yet beautifully, like the strong women of my culture. Her focus isn’t on her body but on the child in her arms. I exaggerated her hair, symbolizing the spiritual power we Natives believe resides in it—our connection to the Earth, our ancestors, and the divine. Even our babies are born with full heads of hair, carrying that power from the moment they arrive.

The baby is inspired by my own son, though depending on the heart of the viewer, it could be a little girl or boy—both precious, both deserving of love and protection. I kept the piece in black and white to create my own version of marble, paying homage to the original material Donatello used.

This recreation is made with admiration and respect for the artist, but also as a ‘brown-washing’ of a world that has so often whitewashed our stories. 
It’s a celebration of Chicano motherhood, strength, and the unwavering hope we have for our children.

 Greenwashing is a marketing ploy to make a product or brand LOOK like it’s clean or non-toxic but it’s really not.

 Sure these brands are better than big name brands BUT they market themselves as “clean” brands yet they have toxic preservatives, synthetic ingredients & “fragrance” or “parfum”.

️The US government has a law that allows companies to hide toxic, hormone-disrupting chemicals under the word “fragrance” or “parfum” to protect the brands “trade secret” scent.

 Some companies will say they use “100% natural” ingredients but did you know that petroleum-based ingredients qualify as “100% natural” & even “organic” because petroleum IS a natural substance that contains carbon because it’s made from rotting leaves from thousands of years ago.

☢️ With all of the chemicals we get exposed to, it becomes even more important to ensure that what we bring into our homes has the least amount of harmful ingredients or none at all!

Esto debería de estar prohibido…
pero se llama: Greenwashing (y cada vez se ve más)

Nos engañan diciendo que las cremas solares no contaminan el mar, que no tienen ciertos ingredientes perjudiciales para los corales y que luego tienen otros super beneficiosos… que si ácido hialuronico para hidratar, que si zanahoria para potenciar tu bronceado… pero en realidad solo han quitado los filtros “más malos” que son los que más dañan a los corales. 

⚠️Siguen usando otros químicos que no están prohibidos, aunque sepa que pueden tener impacto ecológico.

Todo esto es solo un paso hacia algo “menos malo” para el planeta, pero no es lo mismo que un protector 100 % mineral, que es la opción más segura y con menos carga química que deja en el agua.

Además  los términos “Reef-safe” o “ocean respect” no son términos controlados oficialmente. Vamos que cualquiera puede ponerlos en el envase aunque el producto no sea tan respetuoso con el mar como parece.
No hay una ley o sello oficial que diga: “esto sí lo es y esto no”. Por eso, algunas marcas lo usan para parecer más ecológicas de lo que realmente son…

Varias de las sustancias de este tipo de cremas solares, están comprobadas como NO biodegradables y también se acumulan en el mar y en nuestro cuerpo.
Yo personalmente no me fío y los evito al máximo 

➡️ Las mejores opciónes para el mar y para nosotr@s son los solares de óxido de zinc y dióxido de titanio (que ponga sin nano partículas o no nano).

No hay nada perfecto, pero sí mejor para tod@s  

¿Tú también crees que esta publicidad de cremas solares debería estar prohibida?

This might be the title of my memoir…

Wash cold. Inside out. Hang dry. 

⬆️ This is how you wash your blue jeans

Did you know that denim is on trend??

I don’t think that denim is ever ‘off trend’ - but the fact that it’s on trend means that you’ll find denim in tons of iterations out there. 

Maxi skirts. Denim blazers. Cargo jeans. Denim accessories. 

And so many options in jeans. 

So, if you want to keep your blue denim blue (I feel like I’m in a laundry commercial), follow my advice. 

Because if you don’t wash cold-inside out-hang dry ➡️ your jeans will fade much faster. And you don’t want that, right?

And this doesn’t just go for blue jeans. I advise this for black jeans. And grey jeans. And basically any color that you don’t want to fade.

The reason this might be on my memoir title is because I say it ALL THE TIME. Pretty much to every new client. And sometimes more than once to the same client 

SAVE THIS POST so you remember this advice. #denimcare #howtowashjeans #stylisttips #bayareastylist

This is a 4th generation dry cleaner's explanation of liquid bluing. Liquid bluing cancels out the yellow tones of certain stains, like body oil, with a tiny bit of blue dye. This is the same reason most laundry detergents are blue! However, liquid bluing does not actually remove the cause of yellow staining on sheets and towels (body oil / sebum), it simply covers it up. I like to think of liquid bluing as make up. To properly address old yellow stains on your garments, first treat with some water and dish soap, wash as recommended by the care label, and then treat with oxygen bleach. The pretreatment will remove any body oils and the oxygen bleach (also known as color safe bleach) will fix the color. Pinkwashing happens when companies or organizations use breast cancer awareness as a marketing tactic without creating meaningful impact. But it’s not just about selling pink products without donating—pinkwashing can also occur when a company, organization, or event encourages people to "wear pink" for awareness, but stops short of driving real action, like education or fundraising. To spot pinkwashing, ask yourself: Are they providing information about breast cancer? Is there a clear statement on how much is being donated and where it's going, or are they simply focused on the color pink? True awareness means inspiring action, not just wearing or buying a color. If you’ve ever participated in pinkwashing unintentionally, it's okay—we all learn and grow! The goal is to move from awareness to real action. Share resources that educate, donate directly to impactful organizations, and inspire others to support breast cancer initiatives in meaningful ways. When we know better, we do better.  And if you're looking for inspiration on how to make a difference, consider supporting some of my favorite organizations that contribute to both the fight against breast cancer and support those affected: @fit4acause_strong - This NH-based organization raises funds for local breast cancer patients and survivors through fitness events, fostering a supportive community. @runway4recovery - Runway for Recovery supports New England families who have lost a caregiver to breast cancer or have a caregiver with metastatic breast cancer, by providing substantial financial aid. They also offer community support for survivors, pre-vivors, and legacies at an annual fashion show. @danafarber - As a leading cancer research and treatment center in Boston, Dana Farber focuses on cutting-edge research, patient care, and education. @metavivor - METAvivor is dedicated to funding research for metastatic breast cancer (MBC) and provides support and advocacy for those living with MBC, ensuring that this often-overlooked group receives the attention and resources they deserve. @afreshchapter - This organization offers personal growth programs for cancer patients and survivors, helping them heal emotionally, rediscover their passions, and connect with others to build resilience and create a positive future. #KnowBetterDoBetter #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth #MoveBeyondPink #pinkwashing #breastcancer #breastcancereducation #takeaction #themoreyouknow #breastcancersurvivor #beware #october #comingsoon

Wat is nou eigenlijk écht gezond? 

Dat transparantie NIET voorop staat in de voedingsindustrie moge duidelijk zijn. 

Daarom is het extra belangrijk je erg bewust te zijn van wat je koopt en waar je naar moet kijken.

Health Wassing is iets wat helaas veel voorkomt. Een product lijkt gezond maar als je het etiket gaat lezen is dat het niet. 

@manonsfoodfacts let bij elk product op iets anders als ze het etiket leest
 Bij graansoorten let ze op de hoeveelheid vezels en NIET op calorieën.
 Bij groentes en fruit hoef je het etiket niet te lezen.
 En een belangrijke tip: zorg dat de producten die je koopt MINDER dan 5 ingrediënten hebben, dan staan ze het dichtst bij de natuur. 

Meer tips? Houd @goldeahealth in de gaten. De aankomende tijd delen we kennis voor een gezondere levensstijl .

Lesser-Known Tricks for Washing Down Jackets! ✨ Tired of clumpy, yellowed, or stained down jackets after washing? Don’t worry! Follow these pro tips to keep your jacket fluffy, clean, and like new!  1. Say No to Clumping! ✔️ Best for: Keeping the jacket’s fluffiness  Hack: Toss tennis balls or rolled-up socks into the dryer! 1️⃣ Wash your jacket on a gentle cycle with cold water. 2️⃣ Put it in the dryer with two or three tennis balls. 3️⃣ Dry on low heat—the balls help redistribute feathers and prevent clumping!  2. Remove Yellowing from White Down Jackets ✔️ Best for: Yellowed or dull jackets  Hack: Use potassium permanganate + vinegar 1️⃣ Dissolve a few grains of potassium permanganate in warm water (light pink color). 2️⃣ Soak the jacket for 10 minutes to remove yellowing. 3️⃣ Rinse, then soak in vinegar water for 5 minutes. 4️⃣ Wash as usual—your jacket will be bright and fresh again!  3. The No-Wash Spot Cleaning Trick ✔️ Best for: Small stains and oil spots  Hack: Use toothpaste + baking soda 1️⃣ Mix equal parts toothpaste and baking soda into a paste. 2️⃣ Apply to stains and gently scrub with an old toothbrush. 3️⃣ Wipe clean with a damp cloth—no need for a full wash!  4. Proper Washing Method ✔️ Best for: Preventing damage, feather loss, and stiffness  Hack: Use shampoo instead of harsh detergents! 1️⃣ Hand wash with mild shampoo (it’s gentler than laundry detergent). 2️⃣ Submerge the jacket in lukewarm water and gently press to clean. 3️⃣ Rinse thoroughly—leftover soap can make feathers sticky!  Avoid: ❌ Strong detergents (they strip natural oils from feathers). ❌ Wringing or twisting (this ruins the down’s structure).  5. The Best Way to Dry It ✔️ Best for: Preventing stiffness & moisture buildup  Hack: Air dry flat in a well-ventilated area. 1️⃣ Hang or lay it flat on a towel (avoid direct sunlight). 2️⃣ Shake the jacket every hour to fluff up the down. 3️⃣ Once dry, toss it in the dryer with tennis balls for a final fluff! ✨ Extra Tips for Long-Lasting Down Jackets: ✅ Store properly: Keep in a breathable bag (not plastic). ✅ Fluff regularly: Gently shake it to keep the feathers evenly distributed. ✅ Spot clean often: Avoid frequent full washes to preserve the insulation. Now your down jacket will be clean, soft, and warm like new! ❄️ Which hack will you try first? ✨ #EasyStainRemoval #DownJacketCleaning #LaundryHacks #FluffyAndClean #StainRemovalHacks

In this episode of can you fix my yellow car!   Client needed his paint cleaned up big time.  Sprinkler system caused a lot of yellow iron and water spots.     We used CarPro Deacale to take care of the water spotting.   Then a good foam bath to neutralize that product and help remove any dirt and grime left over.    Then we went on to clay the vehicle using a synthetic clay towel and sponge.   After that step we had a nice smooth surface but, we still had a yellow car!    So on to the next step of iron removal.   We hit it with Purple X iron remover from Superior Products.   In the pictures the product will turn purple as it reacts to iron.    This will lift the iron from the paint.    We then rinsed away the product panel by panel.   Dwell time for the product was 1-3 minutes.   Some slight agitation was used to aid in the harder areas where the iron was really holding onto the paint.   After we all the way around the vehicle we then foamed the car down again and proceeded to wash the vehicle one last time to make sure we got all of the previous chemicals and grime completely removed from the vehicle.   We sealed the paint with Koch Chemie Hydro sealant.    Client was very pleased with the results.   We will see him back in a few weeks to maintenance wash and add a topper to keep his ride protected.    #cardetailing #brianscompleteautodetailingllc #kochchemieusa #superiorproducts

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl**

Get ready for a flavor explosion with this incredible Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl! Perfect for a cozy night in or impressing your guests, this dish is a vibrant and mouthwatering experience you won't forget.

**Ingredients:**

- 1 1/2 lbs chicken breast
- 3 cups flour
- Peanut oil (for frying)
- 1/2 cup corn starch
- 1 red bell pepper, diced
- 1 can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained
- 1 can of black beans, rinsed and drained
- 1 can of red kidney beans, rinsed and drained
- 1 red onion, finely diced
- 1 cucumber, diced (peeling is optional)
- 1 cup bulgur, cooked to perfection
- 1 cup couscous, cooked and fluffy
- Green onion for a fresh garnish
- Lime wedges for that zesty kick

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Sauce:**

- 1 Tbsp minced garlic
- 2 Tbsp minced yellow onion
- 1/2 stick of unsalted butter
- 3 1/2 Tbsp raw honey
- 1/4 cup sweet chili sauce
- 3 Tbsp Frank’s Hot Sauce
- 1 Tbsp sriracha
- 1 tsp onion powder
- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 2 Tbsp rice wine vinegar
- Salt and pepper to taste

**Let’s Get Cooking!**

Kick things off by infusing your chicken breast with an array of vibrant flavors! Season it generously with chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cracked pepper, and a sprinkle of sea salt. A splash of avocado oil and a dollop of Greek yogurt will ensure your chicken stays juicy and delicious as it marinates in this flavor bomb!

Next, create a fabulous egg wash and mix your seasoned flour to coat that chicken. The flour should be a reflection of all those delectable spices we just added!

Heat that peanut oil to a sizzling 175 degrees Fahrenheit and watch the magic happen as you dredge your chicken in the egg wash, then in your seasoned flour before frying until it’s golden brown and perfectly crispy.

While the chicken is frying to perfection, let’s prep the colorful medley of beans and veggies! Open those cans, give them a rinse, and let them drain, then chop up that red bell pepper, red onion, cucumber, and get those vibrant green onions ready for garnish.

Now for the pièce de résistance: take those juicy, crispy chicken pieces and toss them in your homemade hot honey sauce! 

Assemble your bowl with layers of flavor, showcasing each ingredient beautifully. Finally, drizzle that mouthwatering hot honey sauce all over your creation, topping it off with a sprinkle of green onion and fresh lime wedges to elevate the taste and appeal.

Your sensational Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl is ready to devour! Enjoy every bite!                                                 #food #fyppppppppppppppppppppppp

What is Greenwashing? #greenwashing #greenwashingsucks #greenwashingalert #sustainability #ecotok #seventhgeneration #ecofriendlyliving

Greenwashing is when a company uses terminology and branding strategies to  make a product appear healthier than it really is. This can include terms like “all natural” or “non-GMO.”

These are some of the most commonly greenwashed products that I would never personally buy!

- Oat milk: oat milk is totally devoid of nutritional value and the oats that are used are heavily contaminated with the pesticide glyphosate. Not to mention most oat milks use canola oil or rapeseed oil as a thickening agent which is super inflammatory
- Seed oils: canola oil, peanut oil, corn oil, vegetable oil blends - these oils are prone to oxidation, high in omega 6 and are incredibly inflammatory to the body. 
- Meat alternatives: most meat alternatives contain a ton of crappy ingredients - including many fillers and additives. Compare a 26 ingredient list and to 1 ingredient in ground beef…if you’re trying to avoid animal products, veggie burgers filled with vegetables are a much cleaner choice than meat alternatives.

The greenwashing about honey bees in native habitats in California needs to stop now. California doesn’t need more bee hives taking crucial food that endangered species like the western bumble bee depend on. Because we are saving the wrong bees. Honey bee numbers continue to grow globally while 1/4 of native bees in North America face extinction. Allowing farmers to leave invasive honey bee hives in native wildflower superblooms habitats has consequences. The extinction of our native pollinators is directly linked to honey bees, and the loss of native habitats like these endangered vernal pool ecosystems. Developers want every vernal pool in California to be a luxury home with grass lawns. Of which only 7% of the vernal pools still remain in California. Just like the way agriculture uses water the way they use honey bees is completely unsustainable. Add that with the growth of suburban sprawl on native land. And that’s why we are living in a extinction crisis. We don’t need more honey bees. We need more native biodiversity. L Black people burning their natural hair in in hopes of straightening it out, and covering their natural curls with straight haired wigs, stems from American culture shunning black people and their features. This is called White Supremacy, and it was a normalized aspect of everyday life in America during slavery (1400s-1865) to the post slavery fight for civil rights era (1865-1969). This cultural shunning was an effort to justify the mistreatment of black people. This shunning involved: •Enslaved Africans were stripped of cultural identity, including hair grooming practices. •Hair was shaved off during capture as a way to “erase” African heritage. •African hair textures were mocked and labeled as “woolly” or “unkempt.” •Dark skin and kinky hair being associated with inferiority; straight, silky hair being associated with “purity” and superiority. •In the 20th century, especially during Jim Crow and after the Great Migration, Black Americans were pressured to conform to Eurocentric beauty norms to secure employment and social mobility. •Straightening hair using hot combs, perms, or chemical relaxers was often necessary to appear “professional.” •Natural hair was considered “unruly,” “militant,” or even “dirty” in schools, workplaces, and media. •For decades, media rarely showed natural Black beauty. •Magazines, films, and music videos glorified lighter skin, straight or wavy hair, and European features. •Wigs and weaves mimicking Eurocentric hair became popular because that was the only way Black women could be accepted in certain industries. Even into the 21st century, there have been countless examples of punishment for wearing natural Black hair: •Children suspended or sent home for locs, braids, or afros. •Adults fired or denied promotions over “unprofessional” hairstyles. •The CROWN Act (Creating a Respectful and Open World for Natural Hair) had to be introduced in 2019 to ban hair-based discrimination in schools and workplaces—a sign of how persistent this issue is. #civilrights  #blackempowerment #civilrights #problack #blackhistorymonth #blackhair #naturalhair #wig #blacktiktok #blacktiktokcommunity

Let’s dive into the science behind hair washing frequency: 

 Sebum Production: Your scalp produces a natural oil called sebum, which keeps your hair moisturized and protected. The amount of sebum produced varies based on genetics, hormones, and even stress levels.

 Hair Texture: The texture of your hair plays a BIG role in how quickly sebum spreads through your hair. Coarse or curly hair slows down this process, meaning you might not need to wash as often. On the other hand, those with fine, straight hair may find their hair gets oily faster, so they may need to wash more frequently.

 Skin Type: Normal to dry skin and hair types might only need to wash once or twice a week. If you have an oily scalp, you may need to wash your hair more often to manage the grease.

 Scalp Health: Washing your hair also means keeping your scalp clean. Skipping shampoos for too long can lead to a buildup of dead skin and oil, which can cause discomfort and issues like dermatitis or dandruff.

So even though there’s no one-size-fits-all answer, a good rule of thumb is to wash your hair when it feels like it needs it, which could be anywhere from every 2-3 days to once a week, depending on your individual hair and scalp. I love Jelly Babies, but the only brand that I can find is made by a company that promises “healthy” sweets.  Upon closer inspection, they are exactly the same as standard Jelly Babies, but the bag is trying to either shame me into eating fewer of them, or trying to trick me into thinking I ate less than I did.  This is called “healthwashing”. 

This can involve emphasizing a specific nutrient or health benefit of a product. For example, a high-sugar cereal might claim to be "a good source of vitamin C" to divert attention from its sugar content

Manipulating serving sizes, or portion distortion, to make a product appear lower in calories, fat, or sugar than it actually is.  Like my Jelly babies!!  Nobody is stopping after 6 measly Jelly Babies.

Some companies use influencers, celebrities, or health experts to endorse their products, giving the impression that these products are backed by health professionals. However, these endorsements may be paid for or lack scientific credibility.  Some “wellness influencers” also demonize normal foods in order to sell the foods or supplements for which they get endorsements. 

It's essential for consumers to be aware of these healthwashing tactics and rely on evidence-based information and transparent labeling to make informed choices about their food, products, and services.  And most importantly eat the food that you enjoy, instead of the one with some nebulous health claims.  If you’re craving a cookie, eat a cookie, rather than eating a bunch of “low fat” cookies that probably don’t taste that good and then eating the cookie you wanted anyway.  I will continue to eat jelly babies, because I love them, but I know that most of the time I will be eating the serving size on the normal ones and not the one marketed as being sensible (whatever that means).

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl** Get ready for a flavor explosion with this incredible Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl! Perfect for a cozy night in or impressing your guests, this dish is a vibrant and mouthwatering experience you won't forget. **Ingredients:** - 1 1/2 lbs chicken breast - 3 cups flour - Peanut oil (for frying) - 1/2 cup corn starch - 1 red bell pepper, diced - 1 can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained - 1 can of black beans, rinsed and drained - 1 can of red kidney beans, rinsed and drained - 1 red onion, finely diced - 1 cucumber, diced (peeling is optional) - 1 cup bulgur, cooked to perfection - 1 cup couscous, cooked and fluffy - Green onion for a fresh garnish - Lime wedges for that zesty kick **Hot Honey Sweet Chili Sauce:** - 1 Tbsp minced garlic - 2 Tbsp minced yellow onion - 1/2 stick of unsalted butter - 3 1/2 Tbsp raw honey - 1/4 cup sweet chili sauce - 3 Tbsp Frank’s Hot Sauce - 1 Tbsp sriracha - 1 tsp onion powder - 1/2 tsp garlic powder - 2 Tbsp rice wine vinegar - Salt and pepper to taste **Let’s Get Cooking!** Kick things off by infusing your chicken breast with an array of vibrant flavors! Season it generously with chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cracked pepper, and a sprinkle of sea salt. A splash of avocado oil and a dollop of Greek yogurt will ensure your chicken stays juicy and delicious as it marinates in this flavor bomb! Next, create a fabulous egg wash and mix your seasoned flour to coat that chicken. The flour should be a reflection of all those delectable spices we just added! Heat that peanut oil to a sizzling 175 degrees Fahrenheit and watch the magic happen as you dredge your chicken in the egg wash, then in your seasoned flour before frying until it’s golden brown and perfectly crispy. While the chicken is frying to perfection, let’s prep the colorful medley of beans and veggies! Open those cans, give them a rinse, and let them drain, then chop up that red bell pepper, red onion, cucumber, and get those vibrant green onions ready for garnish. Now for the pièce de résistance: take those juicy, crispy chicken pieces and toss them in your homemade hot honey sauce!  Assemble your bowl with layers of flavor, showcasing each ingredient beautifully. Finally, drizzle that mouthwatering hot honey sauce all over your creation, topping it off with a sprinkle of green onion and fresh lime wedges to elevate the taste and appeal. Your sensational Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl is ready to devour! Enjoy every bite!                                                 #food #fyppppppppppppppppppppppp

Homemade Blackwash Ingredients:
1. Funnel
2 An empty bottle
3. Black ink (we used Liquitex Acrylic ink in Carbon Black)
4. Disposable shot glasses
5. Varnish (we used Liquitex Acrylic mediums satin varnish)
* Note: the type of varnish used will affect the finish of your wash once dry use the type of varnish you desire to get the result you want
6. Airbrush medium (we used Liquitex Acrylic mediums Airbrush medium)
7. Water
8. Dishwashing soap diluted with water
* Note: this also acts as a flow aid

Recipe:
1. Get 4 shot glasses
2. fill 1 with airbrush medium (make sure to shake the bottle well!), 1 with varnish and 2 with water that contains some of the diluted dishwashing soap
3. Add 10 drops of black ink into each of the shot glasses with Airbrush medium and Varnish respectively and mix with a stirrer (This is for a soft tone not a strong tone black)
4. Pour all the wet ingredients into your empty bottle with the funnel
5. Repeat steps 1-4 until the bottle is full
6. Test the wash on a model
7. Add more drops of black ink to your mix to increase the darkness to your desired level (we added 15 more drops)

Try it out and hope you enjoy it!

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl**

Get ready for a flavor explosion with this incredible Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl! Perfect for a cozy night in or impressing your guests, this dish is a vibrant and mouthwatering experience you won't forget.

**Ingredients:**

- 1 1/2 lbs chicken breast
- 3 cups flour
- Peanut oil (for frying)
- 1/2 cup corn starch
- 1 red bell pepper, diced
- 1 can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained
- 1 can of black beans, rinsed and drained
- 1 can of red kidney beans, rinsed and drained
- 1 red onion, finely diced
- 1 cucumber, diced (peeling is optional)
- 1 cup bulgur, cooked to perfection
- 1 cup couscous, cooked and fluffy
- Green onion for a fresh garnish
- Lime wedges for that zesty kick

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Sauce:**

- 1 Tbsp minced garlic
- 2 Tbsp minced yellow onion
- 1/2 stick of unsalted butter
- 3 1/2 Tbsp raw honey
- 1/4 cup sweet chili sauce
- 3 Tbsp Frank’s Hot Sauce
- 1 Tbsp sriracha
- 1 tsp onion powder
- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 2 Tbsp rice wine vinegar
- Salt and pepper to taste

**Let’s Get Cooking!**

Kick things off by infusing your chicken breast with an array of vibrant flavors! Season it generously with chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cracked pepper, and a sprinkle of sea salt. A splash of avocado oil and a dollop of Greek yogurt will ensure your chicken stays juicy and delicious as it marinates in this flavor bomb!

Next, create a fabulous egg wash and mix your seasoned flour to coat that chicken. The flour should be a reflection of all those delectable spices we just added!

Heat that peanut oil to a sizzling 175 degrees Fahrenheit and watch the magic happen as you dredge your chicken in the egg wash, then in your seasoned flour before frying until it’s golden brown and perfectly crispy.

While the chicken is frying to perfection, let’s prep the colorful medley of beans and veggies! Open those cans, give them a rinse, and let them drain, then chop up that red bell pepper, red onion, cucumber, and get those vibrant green onions ready for garnish.

Now for the pièce de résistance: take those juicy, crispy chicken pieces and toss them in your homemade hot honey sauce! 

Assemble your bowl with layers of flavor, showcasing each ingredient beautifully. Finally, drizzle that mouthwatering hot honey sauce all over your creation, topping it off with a sprinkle of green onion and fresh lime wedges to elevate the taste and appeal.

Your sensational Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl is ready to devour! Enjoy every bite!                                                 #food #fyppppppppppppppppppppppp

We are two-ish weeks out from breast cancer awareness month and the community has suffered some tough losses recently. Losses that make this October feel heavier, more important, and in many ways more infuriating. This is my first year as a survivor and I have two main thoughts: 1. Stage 4 needs more 2. Corporate greed and pinkwashing is out of control If you’re replacing necessary purchases with those that contribute to the cause by all means, go pink… but if you’re going out of your way to try and make a difference this October by making incremental pink purchases, your money is likely better spent as a direct donation to orgs like Metavivor, V Foundation, or Breast Cancer Research Foundation.

Then make sure to SHARE IT with someone who may need this or that may benefit from this information. 
➡️ Bleach doesn’t really whiten your clothes it actually removes colors and some stains. Overtime what will happen is that you will start to notice your white laundry will turn yellow. Same thing goes if you use hot water. Hot water will also shorten the lifespan of your laundry, will shrink garments, they will look dingy over time and you also use more electricity. For those who don’t air out their machines and use hot water… that’s a breeding ground for mold & bacteria. So always use cold.

Did you know this? 

Caution: Potential Harm in Store-Bought Body Soaps!

Be Informed Before You Lather Up!

Did you know that many body soaps available in stores can contain harmful ingredients that may impact your well-being?

Behind their appealing packaging, these products often contain harsh chemicals like sulfates, parabens, synthetic fragrances, and artificial colors.

These ingredients have been associated with skin irritation, dryness, allergic reactions, and disruptions to your body's natural balance.

To safeguard your skin and overall health, consider opting for safer alternatives such as natural, organic, or handmade body soaps. Embrace the benefits of nourishing botanicals and gentle formulations that pamper your skin without compromising your well-being.

Remember, every shower is an opportunity to prioritize your body's care. Make informed choices and steer clear of potential hazards!

W świecie beauty pojęcie „washing” odnosi się do różnych technik marketingowych, które mają na celu kreowanie pozytywnego wizerunku marki, czasem w sposób wprowadzający konsumentów w błąd. Najczęściej występujące rodzaje washingu w branży beauty to:

1. Greenwashing – To praktyka, w której marka twierdzi, że jej produkty są ekologiczne lub przyjazne środowisku, podczas gdy w rzeczywistości te zapewnienia są wyolbrzymione lub nieprawdziwe. Przykładem może być promowanie kosmetyków jako „naturalnych” lub „organicznych”, nawet jeśli składniki te stanowią tylko niewielki procent produktu.

2. Cleanwashing – Dotyczy promowania kosmetyków jako „czystych” lub „non-toxic”, sugerując, że są one pozbawione szkodliwych substancji chemicznych. W praktyce często brakuje rzetelnych dowodów na poparcie tych twierdzeń, a produkty mogą zawierać składniki, które nie są faktycznie „czyste” czy bezpieczne.

3. Ethical washing – Zdarza się, że marki reklamują się jako etyczne, np. twierdząc, że wspierają prawa zwierząt lub lokalne społeczności, chociaż ich działania są powierzchowne. Na przykład firma może promować swoje produkty jako cruelty-free, ale być związana z testami na zwierzętach w krajach, gdzie są one wymagane.

4. Healthwashing – Praktyka ta polega na przedstawianiu kosmetyków jako zdrowotnie korzystnych, podczas gdy nie mają one realnego wpływu na zdrowie użytkowników. Produkty te mogą zawierać substancje takie jak witaminy lub antyoksydanty, lecz w ilościach zbyt małych, aby miały rzeczywisty efekt.

5. Pinkwashing – Związany z promowaniem wsparcia dla społeczności LGBTQ+, bez faktycznego zaangażowania lub realnego wsparcia. Marka może używać symboliki tęczy lub deklarować swoje poparcie, ale nie wprowadzać konkretnych działań wspierających tę społeczność.

Te strategie mogą skutecznie przyciągnąć klientów, którzy kierują się wartościami proekologicznymi lub etycznymi, jednak mogą być mylące, jeśli brak transparentności i realnych działań w firmach.

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl** Get ready for a flavor explosion with this incredible Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl! Perfect for a cozy night in or impressing your guests, this dish is a vibrant and mouthwatering experience you won't forget. **Ingredients:** - 1 1/2 lbs chicken breast - 3 cups flour - Peanut oil (for frying) - 1/2 cup corn starch - 1 red bell pepper, diced - 1 can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained - 1 can of black beans, rinsed and drained - 1 can of red kidney beans, rinsed and drained - 1 red onion, finely diced - 1 cucumber, diced (peeling is optional) - 1 cup bulgur, cooked to perfection - 1 cup couscous, cooked and fluffy - Green onion for a fresh garnish - Lime wedges for that zesty kick **Hot Honey Sweet Chili Sauce:** - 1 Tbsp minced garlic - 2 Tbsp minced yellow onion - 1/2 stick of unsalted butter - 3 1/2 Tbsp raw honey - 1/4 cup sweet chili sauce - 3 Tbsp Frank’s Hot Sauce - 1 Tbsp sriracha - 1 tsp onion powder - 1/2 tsp garlic powder - 2 Tbsp rice wine vinegar - Salt and pepper to taste **Let’s Get Cooking!** Kick things off by infusing your chicken breast with an array of vibrant flavors! Season it generously with chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cracked pepper, and a sprinkle of sea salt. A splash of avocado oil and a dollop of Greek yogurt will ensure your chicken stays juicy and delicious as it marinates in this flavor bomb! Next, create a fabulous egg wash and mix your seasoned flour to coat that chicken. The flour should be a reflection of all those delectable spices we just added! Heat that peanut oil to a sizzling 175 degrees Fahrenheit and watch the magic happen as you dredge your chicken in the egg wash, then in your seasoned flour before frying until it’s golden brown and perfectly crispy. While the chicken is frying to perfection, let’s prep the colorful medley of beans and veggies! Open those cans, give them a rinse, and let them drain, then chop up that red bell pepper, red onion, cucumber, and get those vibrant green onions ready for garnish. Now for the pièce de résistance: take those juicy, crispy chicken pieces and toss them in your homemade hot honey sauce!  Assemble your bowl with layers of flavor, showcasing each ingredient beautifully. Finally, drizzle that mouthwatering hot honey sauce all over your creation, topping it off with a sprinkle of green onion and fresh lime wedges to elevate the taste and appeal. Your sensational Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl is ready to devour! Enjoy every bite!                                                 #food #fyppppppppppppppppppppppp

This is a dry cleaners guide for cleaning, whitening, and brightening sheets: 1) Pretreat those high use / yellow areas with dish soap or liquid laundry detergent to tackle the body oil (sebum) stains which cause the yellowing! 2) Add boosters like borax, washing soda, sodium percarbonate (powdered oxygen bleach), and baking soda to the drum of your machine (ideally before you load clothing). Play around with the ratios and find what's best for you. 3) Rinse products are a nice touch but are not necessary 4) Adding more powdered oxygen bleach every once in a while is wise as well 5) Soak your sheets (towels too) in hot hot water (ideally 140 F / 60 C) overnight with powdered oxygen bleach. Oxygen bleach, unlike chlorine bleach, takes a long time to work and loves heat. 6) If you don't have the ability to soak your sheets try spraying them with hydrogen peroxide and air drying them inside / in the shade 7) Rewash and enjoy your squeaky clean sheets #laundry #cleansheets #howtowhitensheets #whitesheets #howtocleansheets #cleanbedding #howtocleanbedding #howtowhitenbedding #drycleaningtips #experttips #laundrytips #laundryhacks #howto #explained #laundrytok

You should know that sebum is the cause of yellow stains on your clothing. Sebum is an oily substance that protects your skin and hair and is produced by the sebaceous glands. Your body produces about 40 grams of sebum every day which means it's the most common and prevalent stain on your clothes!!! Overtime, sebum oxidizes (turns yellow) when exposed to air. This is the same reaction that occurs to an apple or avocado when cut into.  Soooooo here are some tips from a 4th generation dry cleaner on how to prevent and remove* sebum / old yellow stains. *This guide will also work for any old stain that you haven't had luck removing!  Sebum is an oily stain, so do what you normally would do for a greasy stain. I'd pretreat it with your favorite stain remover, laundry detergent or a high quality dish soap. Plus, the sooner you get to it the better (less time for it to oxidize).  Once you've addressed the root of the issue you'll need to fix the color. To do this use an oxygen bleach like hydrogen peroxide or powdered oxygen bleach (OxiClean). To remove with hydrogen peroxide, spray it on the stained areas and let it air dry inside (HP and UV rays do not vibe). To remove it with powdered oxygen bleach, soak your entire garment in hot water and powdered oxygen bleach (ideally 140 F / 60 C and above) overnight. The second method is a great way to keep sheets and towels bright and white as well (you only need to do this once or twice a year).  Oxygen bleach is also known as color safe bleach or nonchlorine bleach. It's sooooo much gentler on your clothing too! The one drawback is it takes a while to work, so patience is key. You may need to repeat this process for severe staining. I also recommend washing after using either of these methods. For more tips on stain removal check out thecleanclub.com Anyways I hope this guide helps :) #sebum #oilstain #greasestain #yellowstain #stainremoval #stain #laundry #laundrytip #laundryhack #cleaning #clean #cleaninghack

So we’ve all been putting it off… huh? 

Washing your down jackets is definitely a process, but it’s not difficult! 

I think it can be really scary to wash them because they’re so expensive, and it’s totally possible to ruin them, BUT if you use the right products and have some patience, you’re going to be just fine!

Here are the steps:

 Clean stains: make sure you scrub any stains ahead of washing with the @nikwaxna down wash (the same wash for the first cycle). Also do a once over for any holes before watching and patch them!

 1st wash: if you have a top loader, zip all of the pockets and place the jacket in a mesh bag (you can skip the bag if you have a front loader). Wash the jacket with Nikwax Down Wash (the bottle will tell you measurements) on a delicate cycle on medium/low temps. 

☔️ 2nd wash: waterproofing. Use Nikwax Down Proof to give the jacket a water repellancy. Same temps and wash type. 

 Dry: dry on low heat with a few tennis or wool balls to get rid of the clumps of down. This will take quite a few cycles, and you’ll know it’s done when it’s puffy again and the clumps are gone!

(This isn’t an ad, but Nikwax products are what we use for all of our gear care, they’re environmentally friendly, and they make gear last WAY longer)

Perfect for a cozy night in or impressing your guests, this dish is a vibrant and mouthwatering experience you won't forget. **Ingredients:** - 1 1/2 lbs chicken breast - 3 cups flour - Peanut oil (for frying) - 1/2 cup corn starch - 1 red bell pepper, diced - 1 can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained - 1 can of black beans, rinsed and drained - 1 can of red kidney beans, rinsed and drained - 1 red onion, finely diced - 1 cucumber, diced (peeling is optional) - 1 cup bulgur, cooked to perfection - 1 cup couscous, cooked and fluffy - Green onion for a fresh garnish - Lime wedges for that zesty kick **Hot Honey Sweet Chili Sauce:** - 1 Tbsp minced garlic - 2 Tbsp minced yellow onion - 1/2 stick of unsalted butter - 3 1/2 Tbsp raw honey - 1/4 cup sweet chili sauce - 3 Tbsp Frank’s Hot Sauce - 1 Tbsp sriracha - 1 tsp onion powder - 1/2 tsp garlic powder - 2 Tbsp rice wine vinegar - Salt and pepper to taste **Let’s Get Cooking!** Kick things off by infusing your chicken breast with an array of vibrant flavors! Season it generously with chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cracked pepper, and a sprinkle of sea salt. A splash of avocado oil and a dollop of Greek yogurt will ensure your chicken stays juicy and delicious as it marinates in this flavor bomb! Next, create a fabulous egg wash and mix your seasoned flour to coat that chicken. The flour should be a reflection of all those delectable spices we just added! Heat that peanut oil to a sizzling 175 degrees Fahrenheit and watch the magic happen as you dredge your chicken in the egg wash, then in your seasoned flour before frying until it’s golden brown and perfectly crispy. While the chicken is frying to perfection, let’s prep the colorful medley of beans and veggies! Open those cans, give them a rinse, and let them drain, then chop up that red bell pepper, red onion, cucumber, and get those vibrant green onions ready for garnish. Now for the pièce de résistance: take those juicy, crispy chicken pieces and toss them in your homemade hot honey sauce!  Assemble your bowl with layers of flavor, showcasing each ingredient beautifully. Finally, drizzle that mouthwatering hot honey sauce all over your creation, topping it off with a sprinkle of green onion and fresh lime wedges to elevate the taste and appeal. Your sensational Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl is ready to devour! Enjoy every bite!                                                 #food #fyppppppppppppppppppppppp

* O greenwashing é uma ação que empresas realizam para "maquiar" os seus produtos e tentar passar a ideia de que eles são ecoeficientes, ambientalmente corre tos, provêm de processos sustentáveis, entre outros. Assim, termos e expressões como “eco”, “ecológico”, “menos poluente” e “sustentável” começam a aparecer nas embalagens e rótulos de diversos produtos, na tentativa de indicar que as empresas são ambientalmente responsáveis.[6]

* Essa demanda muitas vezes gera procedimentos incorretos, em que se incluem informações falsas, irrelevantes ou confusas, que fazem com que o consumidor tenha ceticismo para com os produtos "verdes" e se mostre confuso aquando da escolha ou avaliação entre produtos de empresas realmente "verdes" e outras que primam pelas ações do greenwashing. Logo, o greenwashing, além de não fornecer qualquer contributo positivo para o meio ambiente, ainda gera desconfiança nos consumidores, afastando-os dos produtos, de facto, ambientalmente corretos.

Did you know that washing your backflow protectors after every pumping session is essential for maintaining optimal hygiene?  Let's dive into why it's so important!   Potential Milk Contact: The pumping journey can get messy, and it's not uncommon for milk drops to splash onto the backflow protectors. These tiny splatters can lead to bacterial growth if left uncleaned. By washing them thoroughly, you're ensuring a clean and safe pumping experience for you and your little one.  ️ Condensation Concerns: Our bodies go through temperature changes during pumping, which can cause condensation to form inside the backflow protectors. This moisture, if not properly addressed, can become a breeding ground for bacteria. Regular washing helps prevent any unwanted microbial buildup and keeps your pumping routine worry-free.  Proper Cleaning Ritual: To maintain optimal hygiene, simply dissemble your backflow protectors and all other parts that come in contact with breast milk (tubing never needs to be washed). Rinse all parts thoroughly and allow to air dry before reassembling. Remember, clean equipment means a healthier pumping journey!   Spectra Cares: We're committed to your well-being and that of your little one. By advocating for proper cleaning practices, we're ensuring that your pumping sessions remain as safe and hygienic as possible. Together, let's prioritize cleanliness and enjoy peace of mind during your breastfeeding journey.   Discover more pumping tips, expert advice, and innovative breastfeeding solutions at Spectra Baby USA! ⭐️ Source:  Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. (2023, December 14). How to keep your breast pump kit clean: The essentials. U.S. Department of Health & Human Services. #Spectra #spectrapump #pumpingmom

This is what I learned about body washes recently- Several ingredients commonly found in body washes can be harmful to human health: 1. **Sulfates (Sodium Lauryl Sulfate and Sodium Laureth Sulfate)**: These can cause skin irritation, dryness, and strip natural oils from the skin. 2. **Parabens**: Used as preservatives, they have been linked to hormone disruption and potentially to breast cancer. 3. **Phthalates**: Often used to enhance fragrance, they are known endocrine disruptors and have been linked to reproductive issues. 4. **Synthetic Fragrances**: Can contain numerous chemicals that may cause allergies, skin irritation, and respiratory issues. 5. **Triclosan**: An antibacterial agent that can contribute to antibiotic resistance and has potential endocrine-disrupting effects. 6. **Formaldehyde and Formaldehyde-Releasing Preservatives**: These are known carcinogens and can cause skin irritation. 7. **Polyethylene Glycol (PEG)**: Often contaminated with impurities like ethylene oxide and 1,4-dioxane, both of which are potential carcinogens. 8. **Dioxane**: A contaminant found in some detergents and cleansers that is a probable human carcinogen. 9. **Artificial Colors**: These can cause skin irritation and allergic reactions and some are suspected to be carcinogenic. 10. **Methylisothiazolinone (MIT) and Methylchloroisothiazolinone (CMIT)**: Preservatives that can cause allergic reactions and skin irritation. Choosing products with natural, organic, and fewer synthetic ingredients can help mitigate these health risks. Comment BW and I’ll send you my fav body wash with a discount

Say NO to chlorine bleach. ‍♀️ It’s harsh on laundry and will weaken fibers, so your items will be more prone to holes. It can also contribute to yellowing overtime.  To keep your whites white, we recommend using an oxygen brightener instead of bleach. You’ll find this product on the market under a variety of names like "oxygen whitener", "oxygen brightener" or "bleach alternative", to name a few.  Oxygen brighteners use sodium percarbonate to break down organic compounds and help detergent penetrate deeper into the fabric.  They effectively whiten graying or yellowing whites, and have a brightening effect on colors (unlike bleach, oxygen brightener is color-safe). ️ As for water temperature, always choose the hottest temperature that the garment can withstand if your goal is to whiten. Check the care labels and wash accordingly.  And last but not least, air dry outside! Take advantage of the sun’s UV rays to brighten your white laundry naturally. –  Learn with #thelaundrysisters #learn #laundry #laundrytips #laundryhacks #celsious #laundrytok #bleach #cleaningtiktok

Why does this matter? Greenwashing and climate denial share a core objective: to postpone the emission cuts urgently required to avert climate breakdown. [II] Whereas denial invites opposition, greenwashing lulls the public into believing problems are already solved. Under this collective illusion, pressure on high-emitting firms evaporates and the radical decisions needed to transform energy, transport, and food systems are delayed indefinitely. [IV] Greenwashing thus acts as a soothing lullaby, leading society toward ecological ruin with a tune of comforting half-truths. Exposing this deception is essential if clichés are to be replaced by real, measurable emission cuts.

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl**

Get ready for a flavor explosion with this incredible Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl! Perfect for a cozy night in or impressing your guests, this dish is a vibrant and mouthwatering experience you won't forget.

**Ingredients:**

- 1 1/2 lbs chicken breast
- 3 cups flour
- Peanut oil (for frying)
- 1/2 cup corn starch
- 1 red bell pepper, diced
- 1 can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained
- 1 can of black beans, rinsed and drained
- 1 can of red kidney beans, rinsed and drained
- 1 red onion, finely diced
- 1 cucumber, diced (peeling is optional)
- 1 cup bulgur, cooked to perfection
- 1 cup couscous, cooked and fluffy
- Green onion for a fresh garnish
- Lime wedges for that zesty kick

**Hot Honey Sweet Chili Sauce:**

- 1 Tbsp minced garlic
- 2 Tbsp minced yellow onion
- 1/2 stick of unsalted butter
- 3 1/2 Tbsp raw honey
- 1/4 cup sweet chili sauce
- 3 Tbsp Frank’s Hot Sauce
- 1 Tbsp sriracha
- 1 tsp onion powder
- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 2 Tbsp rice wine vinegar
- Salt and pepper to taste

**Let’s Get Cooking!**

Kick things off by infusing your chicken breast with an array of vibrant flavors! Season it generously with chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, cracked pepper, and a sprinkle of sea salt. A splash of avocado oil and a dollop of Greek yogurt will ensure your chicken stays juicy and delicious as it marinates in this flavor bomb!

Next, create a fabulous egg wash and mix your seasoned flour to coat that chicken. The flour should be a reflection of all those delectable spices we just added!

Heat that peanut oil to a sizzling 175 degrees Fahrenheit and watch the magic happen as you dredge your chicken in the egg wash, then in your seasoned flour before frying until it’s golden brown and perfectly crispy.

While the chicken is frying to perfection, let’s prep the colorful medley of beans and veggies! Open those cans, give them a rinse, and let them drain, then chop up that red bell pepper, red onion, cucumber, and get those vibrant green onions ready for garnish.

Now for the pièce de résistance: take those juicy, crispy chicken pieces and toss them in your homemade hot honey sauce! 

Assemble your bowl with layers of flavor, showcasing each ingredient beautifully. Finally, drizzle that mouthwatering hot honey sauce all over your creation, topping it off with a sprinkle of green onion and fresh lime wedges to elevate the taste and appeal.

Your sensational Hot Honey Sweet Chili Chicken Bowl is ready to devour! Enjoy every bite!                                                 #food #fyppppppppppppppppppppppp

1. Rain Represents Cleansing & Purification ✨

• Spiritually, rain is seen as a natural cleanse — washing away stagnant energy, negativity, and emotional heaviness. ️
• Many cultures view water as a sacred tool for energetic purification, so rain feels like the Earth’s own spiritual reset. 

⸻

2. Connection to Renewal & Rebirth 

• Rain nourishes the Earth, awakens seeds, and brings new life. For spiritual people, this reflects personal growth, healing, and cycles of death & rebirth. ♻️
• It’s a reminder that after drought or difficulty, new beginnings are inevitable — like nature whispering “trust the process.” ✨

⸻

3. Divine Feminine Energy 

• Rain carries deep yin, nurturing, and intuitive energy — often connected to the Divine Feminine, emotional release, and softness. 
• Those aligned with goddess energy, water deities, or emotional healing often feel in tune with rain’s gentle yet powerful presence. ‍♀️✨

⸻

4. Sacred Quiet & Reflection 

• Rain slows life down — the world softens, distractions fade, and people naturally go inward. 
• Rainy days create space for meditation, prayer, reflection, or ritual — perfect for spiritual stillness and heightened awareness. ‍♂️

⸻

5. Emotional Release & Heart Healing ❤️‍

• Just like rain falls from the sky, spiritual people often see it as permission to release tears, grief, or heavy emotions. 
• It symbolizes surrender — crying, purging, and letting go to create space for peace and clarity. ️✨

⸻

6. Symbol of Divine Communication ️

• In many traditions, rain is seen as a blessing, a message, or a sign from ancestors, spirit guides, or the Divine. 
• Rain during meaningful moments (funerals, deep prayer, life transitions) is believed to signal spiritual alignment or presence. 

⸻

7. Earth-Rooted Connection 

• Spiritually connected people feel bonded to nature — rain deepens that connection by touching everything: plants, soil, animals, humans. 
• Walking barefoot in the rain, dancing under it, or simply listening reconnects us to Mother Earth’s energy field.

5 Health Benefits of Cleaning Your Gut Monthly:
#juicingforhealth #phinessegang 
1. Boosts Immune System

️ 70% of your immune system lives in your gut. A clean gut helps your body fight off viruses, bacteria, and chronic inflammation.

2. Improves Mental Clarity & Mood

 Your gut makes over 90% of your serotonin — the “feel good” chemical. A toxic gut can lead to brain fog, anxiety, or depression.

3. Prevents Bloating, Constipation, and IBS

 Monthly gut resets can keep digestion smooth, reduce inflammation, and help avoid long-term gut issues like Irritable Bowel Syndrome (IBS).

4. Reduces Risk of Chronic Disease

❤️ A clean gut lowers your chances of heart disease, diabetes, autoimmune disorders, and even certain cancers by flushing out harmful toxins and waste.

5. Helps with Weight Loss & Hormone Balance

⚖️ A balanced gut supports metabolism and regulates hormones like insulin and cortisol. This can lead to natural weight management and better energy.

The video may be vintage, but the information is still accurate!  Using "quick wash" for every load of laundry can create a detergent buildup inside your washing machine, which can eventually cause the parts to deteriorate prematurely.  Why?  Because the "quick wash" cycle on a washing machine is only designed for 2-4 small items at a time, so if you're using the "quick wash" for a "normal" size load of laundry, the amount of detergent you're using will ALWAYS be too much (which means your machine won't rinse all of it out properly).  When in doubt, always refer to your washing machine's user manual!  #QuickWash #QuickWashCycle #FastWash #FastWashCycle #SpeedWash #WashingMachine #Laundry #LaundryTok #ApplianceRepair #ApplianceCare #ApplianceMaintenance #renduh #WomenInTrades #Tradeswoman #cleanTok #clean #cleaning

When we talk about changing the world, it’s often through what might be seen as “big” things– establishing a nonprofit to help eradicate hunger or increase literacy rates, working on legislation that could end poverty or certain forms of violence...  Or, when we consider growing spiritually, we think about the “most” meaningful time we could spend with God through traditional practices like fasting, bible-reading, or solitude. It’s easy to attribute more value to the moments we think have the greatest impact on the world. And yet, while these are important, our lives typically aren’t made up of really big, or even overtly spiritual, moments. We’re more often engaged in small acts that might go unnoticed and underappreciated. Doing the dishes for your roommates, again. Picking up after the kids, again. Taking out the trash, again. We might begrudgingly complete these tasks, feeling unseen, and wishing for better ways to spend our time. After all, there’s *real* work to be done. But, our Servant Savior showed us that the real work is in our everyday lives. How we showcase love and humility through ordinary service does change the world. How we respond when we’re feeling overworked and undervalued is a Kingdom service. While there are times when we can, and should, advocate for ourselves, here’s a Scripture and a prayer to help us remember the sacred in the mundane.  “Now that I, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you also should wash one another’s feet. I have set you an example that you should do as I have done for you.” (John 13:14-15).       God of the unseen and lowly, thank you for washing me clean. Servant Lord, may my love also be seen in simple, everyday moments. Help me not feel discouraged by monotony, but blessed by the meal you provided and those who shared it with me. In moments where my sacrifices seem unnoticed, help me remember I’m seen by you. Give me peace instead of frustration, humility instead of bitterness, and when I’m feeling overwhelmed, bless me with space to rest in you. Amen.

We’ve been lied to about eco laundry sheets. 
Many laundry sheet brands market their products as “plastic free” despite the fact they literally contain plastic in the form of PVA - a dissolvable plastic. Check the ingredient list for polyvinyl alcohol. 

Most regulatory agencies consider PVA safe as it dissolves in water and biodegrades under the right conditions but studies are conducted in labs, not the real world. And many of these are biased, funded by plastic trade groups. 

Now peer-reviewed studies have found PVA in drinking water and human breast milk. It turns out, more plastic is flowing into the environment than breaking down in water-treatment plants. 

More than that, even if PVA is safe, can we really market something as plastic-free when it contains plastic?

Is Love Beauty and Planet sustainable or is it greenwashing?

Last year I said it was greenwashing, but let’s see if anything has changed. ‍

Welcome to “sustainable or greenwashing month” where everyday leading up to Earth Month I’m sharing if brands and products are actually what they say they are.

Love Beauty and Planet was founded by Unilever in 2018 and influenced by the fast-growing trend for natural ingredients.

They are PETA cruelty free, vegan, paraben and sulfate free, and their packaging uses PCR plastic.

I like how they offer some plastic free items like the shampoo & conditioner bars, & I read a few PR articles about some nonprofits they’ve donated to give back.

As far as sourcing goes, they use fragrance from a company (Givaudan) that has some sustainability initiatives which is definitely better than nothing, But that’s kind of where the sustainability initiatives end. 

I couldn’t  find anything else on their manufacturing processing or ingredient sourcing, or anything of that sort.

They use some odd vague language on their website to address not being perfect and there is this really strange FAQ page that is just copy and paste information for each question which doesn’t even answer the FAQ question to begin with.

OK so, with all of that I think it’s totally greenwashing, too many sketchy things are happening on their website and I don’t even like that it was founded by a major corporation in what sounds like a money grab for people caring about the environment. But what do you think?

This month we’re doing an ENTIRE month of Sustainable or Greenwashing videos, so if there is a brand you want to see, stick around because it’s probably coming.

Is Seventh Generation sustainable or is it greenwashing? 

Welcome to “sustainable or greenwashing month” where everyday leading up to Earth Month I’m sharing if brands and products are actually what they say they are. ️‍♀️

Seventh Generation is a well known household cleaning brand and originally started as a mail-order catalog business that specialized in energy-, water-, and resource-saving products. The name is a reference to a philosophy which says “in our every deliberation, we must consider the impact of our decisions on the next seven generations.” 

The brand is a B Corp, EPA safer choice partner, USDA Certified Biobased, FSC Certified, Leaping Bunny Cruelty Free, plus I like how they have a lot of ingredient disclosure for each product.

Packaging uses a considerable amount of PCR plastic, and Seventh Generation is committed to paying all the workers throughout their supply chain a livable wage. They offer a Annual Corporate Consciousness Report which details their sustainability goals and lays a solid path on how they hope to achieve them, and they also seem to have several nonprofits they work with to give back to communities.

With all of that information, Seventh Generation seems sustainable to me & I love how it’s available and accessible for many people - but what do you think?
